Database.js
1. Creates initial API connection to database/creates if not existing
2. Has some prefill data for shelves
books.js and shelves.js
Endpoints:
GET requests - www.captainsquib.com/api/shelves Grabs all of the shelves as well as the books on each shelf. Returns data as json: [{"id": 2, "shelf_name": "Black", "books": []}] can also be specified to specific shelf id by adding /#
www.captainsquib.com/api/books Grabs all books or by id if specified with /#. Returns data like [{ "id": 6, "name": "Cool", "author": "Weow", "description": "", "genre": "", "timeofaddition": "2026-05-03", "image": "Newbook.png"}]
POST request -
www.captainsquib.com/api/shelves Creates association between a book to a shelf requires json data to have [{"shelfId": 1, "bookId":1}]
www.captainsquib.com/api/books Adds a new book requires json data to have [{"id": 6, "name": "Cool", "author": "Weow", "description": "", "genre": "", "image": "Newbook.png"}
DELETE request -
www.captainsquib.com/api/shelves Deletes association of books to shelves requires json data to have [{"shelfId": 1, "bookId":1}]
